  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A French University team (M. Jeanne, MD, and M. LOGIER, Ph D) have developed a pain
      assessment tool based on the analysis of the variability heart rate which evaluates the
      Analgesia Nociception Index (ANI). This index is intended to give a quantification of pain.

      The aim of the present study is to assess the validity of the ANI parameter in patients with
      Complex Regional Pain Syndrome treated with a nerve block (reversible pain).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
